net.sf.appia.xml.templates
Class ChannelTemplate

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.appia.xml.templates.ChannelTemplate

public class ChannelTemplate
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a channel template. It is used to generate one or more channels that have identical QoS.

Author:
Jose Mocito

addSession

public void addSession(java.lang.String name,
                       int sharing,
                       Layer layer)
Adds a session to the channel template.

First session added corresponds to the bottom most layer.

Parameters:
name - the name of the session.
sharing - the sharing property of the session.
layer - the layer associated with the session.

createChannel

public Channel createChannel(java.lang.String name,
                             java.lang.String label,
                             ChannelProperties params,
                             java.util.Hashtable globalSessions,
                             java.util.Hashtable labelSessions,
                             EventScheduler eventScheduler,
                             MemoryManager memoryManager,
                             JMXConfiguration jmxConfig)
                      throws AppiaXMLException
Creates a channel.

Channel returned is not initialized!

Parameters:
name - the name of the channel.
label - the label of the channel or null if none is defined.
params - the parameters passed to the channel.
globalSessions - Hashtable containing the shared "global sessions".
labelSessions - Hashtable containing the shared "label sessions".
eventScheduler - the EventScheduler associated with the channel.
Returns:
the channel created.
Throws:
AppiaXMLException
